===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The first [[meal]] of the day, [[usually]] [[eat]]en in the [[morning]].
#: {{ux|en|You should put more protein in her '''breakfast''' so she will grow.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 6-2|I|iv|125|2|A ſorry '''Breakfaſt''' for my Lord Protector.}}
#* {{RQ:Travers Cuckoo in the Nest|passage=Peter, after the manner of man at the '''breakfast''' table, had allowed half his kedgeree to get cold and was sniggering over a letter. Sophia looked at him sharply. The only letter she had received was from her mother. Sophia’s mother was not a humourist.}}
# {{lb|en|by extension}} A meal consisting of food [[normally]] eaten in the morning, which may [[typically]] include [[egg]]s, [[sausage]]s, [[toast]], [[bacon]], etc.
#: {{ux|en|We serve '''breakfast''' all day.}}
# The celebratory meal served after a wedding (and occasionally after other solemnities e.g. a funeral).
# {{lb|en|largely|_|obsolete|outside|religion}} A [[meal]] eaten after a period of (now often religious) [[fast]]ing.
#* {{RQ:Dryden Amaryllis}}
#*: The wolves will get a '''breakfast''' by my death.

